properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued January 19 at 3:39AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
West to southwest winds continue to gust to 55 mph early this
morning along the Interstate 80 corridor between Mile Markers 260
to 280. Winds are expected to remain strong for the next several
hours before gradually diminishing after sunrise. Some blowing
snow is also expected, reducing visibilities below 2 miles at
times.

Use caution if traveling through this area this morning,
especially if driving light or high profile vehicles.

NWSheadline: LOCALLY STRONG WINDS CONTINUE ALONG INTERSTATE 80 BETWEEN LARAMIE AND RAWLINS EARLY THIS MORNING
